    "header": "SIMPLE DIFFERENTIAL EQUATIONS",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Solve the equation $4y = x + C$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Separating the variables"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$dy = \\frac{1}{4} (x + C) dx$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "or"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$\\log{(1+y)} = \\frac{1}{4} \\log{(x+C)}$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "if $y$ is written in place of $y$, then"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$\\frac{dy}{dx} = \\frac{1}{4} \\frac{(x + C)}{y}$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Example 5â€”The difference in the tensions at the ends of a belt submitting an angle of $\\theta$ at the center of a pulley of radius $r$ is $T_1 - T_2$, where $\\mu$ is the coefficient of friction between the belt and pulley. If the weight and greatest tensions on the belt are $T_1$ and $T_2$ respectively, whilst the lap is $l$, find an expression for $T_2$."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The equation $T_1 - T_2 = \\mu T_2$."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Integrate both sides of the equation, applying the limits 1 and T to T and 0 to T."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Then"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$\\log{T_1} - \\log{T_2} = \\mu \\log{T_2}$"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$T = \\frac{T_1}{T_2}$."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A word further might be added about Example 3, or a modification to it."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "$T = \\frac{dy}{dx}.$"
      }
    ]
